            <div type="translation">
                <p n="1-6">
                    Cālivākaṉa year 1775,
                    Kaliyuka year 4884,
                    year Cōpakiṟutu, which was then current,
                    month of Āvaṇi, day 30,
                    on the auspicious day when combined a Friday and the <foreign>nakṣatra</foreign> Uttiraṭṭāti.
                </p>
                <p n="6-11">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">This is the</supplied> pious donation <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tārmam</foreign><note>Sanskrit <foreign>dharma</foreign>.</note></supplied> that 
                    Āpatuttāraṇa-ceṭṭiyār, son of Cēṉaikkuṭai Cuppiṟamaṇiya-ceṭṭiyār,
                    gave by making
                    a banner-post and the pavement <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> the temple of Mācilāmaṇiyīcuvaracuvāmi.
                </p>
                <p n="11-12">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">This is made in</supplied>  perpetual devotion.
                </p>
                <p n="12">Let prosperity be!</p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Dated to Śaka 1775 [1853/4 CE] = Kaliyuga 4884 [1783/4 CE] = Jovian cycle year Cōpakiṟutu [1783/4 CE]. Thus Śaka 1775 appears to be a mistake for Śaka 1715 [1783/4 CE].</p>
            </div>
            
